{"timestamp": "2025-12-05 05:31:51.940605", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Submission summary:\n- Anomaly detected: Yes\n- Faulty device(s): web_server_3\n- Root cause(s): sender_application_delay\n\nRationale:\n- Apache (expected HTTP service) is stopped on web_server_3 while a Python BaseHTTP server is listening on port 80, returning 501 to HEAD and causing GET requests to stall until timeout. Network underlay, routing, and DNS are healthy; the issue is isolated to the application layer on the server, matching an application-side delay/failure.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 1828, "output_tokens": 108, "total_tokens": 1936, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 1664}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 0}}}
